## Other Measures of Location: Quartiles, Percentiles, and Trimmed Means

The median (population or sample) divides the data set into two parts of equal size. To obtain finer measures of location, we could divide the data into more than two such parts. Roughly speaking, _quartiles_ divide the data set into four equal parts, with the observations above the third quartile constituting the upper quarter of the data set, the second quartile being identical to the median, and the first quartile

