which becomes

\[P_{k,n}=\frac{n!}{(n-k)!}\]

For example, \(P_{3,9}=9!/(9-3)!=9!/6!=9\cdot 8\cdot 7\cdot 6!/6!=9\cdot 8\cdot 7\). Note also that because \(0!=1\), \(P_{n,n}=n!/(n-n)!=n!/0!=n!/1=n!\), as it should.

