Expand \((x-\mu)^{2}\) in the definition of \(\sigma^{2}\) to obtain \(x^{2}-2\mu x+\mu^{2}\), and then carry \(\Sigma\) through to each of the three terms:

\[\sigma^{2} = \sum_{D}x^{2}\cdot p(x)-2\mu\cdot\sum_{D}x\cdot p(x)+\mu^{2}\sum _{D}p(x)\] \[= E(X^{2})-2\mu\cdot\mu+\mu^{2}=E(X^{2})-\mu^{2}\]

