Let \(X\), the thickness of a membrane, have a uniform distribution on \([A,\,B]\). The density function is shown in Figure 4.6. For \(x<A,\,F(x)=0\), since there is no area under the graph of the density function to the left of such an \(x\). For \(x\geq B,\,F(x)=1\), since all the area is accumulated to the left of such an \(x\). Finally, for \(A\leq x\leq B\),

\[F(x)=\int_{-\infty}^{x}f(y)dy=\int_{A}^{x}\frac{1}{B-A}dy=\frac{1}{B-A}\cdot y \bigg{|}_{y=A}^{y=x}=\frac{x-A}{B-A}\]

The entire cdf is

\[F(x)=\left\{\begin{array}{ll}0&x<A\\ \frac{x-A}{B-A}&A\leq x<B\\ 1&x\geq B\end{array}\right.\]

