\[f_{Y}(y)=f_{X}[h(y)]|h^{\prime}(y)|=f_{X}(x)/f_{X}(x)=1\qquad 0\leq x\leq 1\]

This works because \(h\) and \(F\) are inverse functions, so their derivatives are reciprocals.

