Because the \(t\) distribution is symmetric, it was necessary to tabulate only upper-tail critical values (\(t_{\alpha,v}\) for small values of \(\alpha\)). The chi-squared distribution is not symmetric, so Appendix Table A.6 contains values of \(\chi^{2}_{\alpha,v}\) for \(\alpha\) both near 0 and near 1, as illustrated in Figure 8.9(b). For example, \(\chi^{2}_{\alpha,025,14}\,=\,26.119\) and \(\chi^{2}_{\beta 5,20}\) (the 5th percentile) \(=\,10.851\).

