Of course, when we take a random sample with replacement, repetitions usually occur as they do here, and this implies that not all of the 30 observations will appear in each sample. After doing this 998 more times and computing the means \(\overline{x}_{2}^{*},...,\overline{x}_{999}^{*}\) for these 999 samples, we construct Figure 8.11, the histogram of the 999 \(\overline{x}^{*}\) values.

