Just as the \(P\)-value for a \(z\) test is a \(z\) curve area, the \(P\)-value for a \(t\) test will be a \(t\) curve area. Figure 9.8 illustrates the three different cases. The number of df for the one-sample \(t\) test is \(n\,-\,1\).

