A test procedure for hypotheses concerning the ratio \(\sigma_{1}^{2}/\sigma_{2}^{2}\), as well as a CI for this ratio are based on the following result from Section 6.4.

\[\begin{array}{l} {\text{THEOREM}} & {\text{Let }X_{1},\,\ldots,\,X_{m}\text{ be a random sample from a normal distribution with variance }\sigma_{1}^{2}\text{, let }Y_{1},\,\ldots,\,Y_{n}\text{ be another random sample (independent of the }X_{i}\text{'s) from a normal distribution with variance }\sigma_{2}^{2}\text{, and let }S_{1}^{2}\text{ and }S_{2}^{2}\text{ denote the two sample variances. Then the rv } \\ & F = \frac{S_{1}^{2}/\sigma_{1}^{2}}{S_{2}^{2}/\sigma_{2}^{2}}\]

