The CI for \(\sigma_{1}^{2}/\sigma_{2}^{2}\) is based on replacing \(F\) in the probability statement

\[P(F_{1-\alpha/2,v_{1},v_{2}}<\!F<\!F_{\alpha/2,v_{1},v_{2}})=1-\alpha\]

by the \(F\) variable (10.8) and manipulating the inequalities to isolate \(\sigma_{1}^{2}/\sigma_{2}^{2}\):

\[\frac{s_{1}^{2}}{s_{2}^{2}}\cdot\frac{1}{F_{\alpha/2,v_{1},v_{2}}}<\frac{ \sigma_{1}^{2}}{\sigma_{2}^{2}}<\frac{s_{1}^{2}}{s_{2}^{2}}\cdot\frac{1}{F_{ 1-\alpha/2,v_{1},v_{2}}}=\frac{s_{1}^{2}}{s_{2}^{2}}\cdot F_{\alpha/2,v_{2},v _{1}}\]

