## Testing for Homogeneity

We assume that each individual in every one of the \(I\) populations belongs in exactly one of \(J\) categories. A sample of \(n_{i}\) individuals is taken from the \(i\)th population; let \(n=\sum n_{i}\) and

\(n_{ij}=\) the number of individuals in the \(i\)th sample who fall into category \(j\)

