The \(n_{ij}\)'s are recorded in a two-way contingency table with \(I\) rows and \(J\) columns. The sum of the \(n_{ij}\)'s in the \(i\)th row is \(n_{i}\), whereas the sum of entries in the \(j\)th column is \(n_{j}\).

Let

\(p_{ij}=\) the proportion of the individuals in population \(i\) who fall into category \(j\)

